        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Extended Description</title>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Function</emph>
            </para>
            <para>The Electronic Control Module (ECM) sends a regulated 5 &#177; 0.5 volt voltage reference to engine
                and vehicle control sensors. The sensor signals are compared to the Voltage Reference to determine
                sensor output (actual signal values). These values are processed by the ECM for engine operation.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Operation</emph>
            </para>
            <para>The ECM supplies V
                <subscript>REF</subscript>Voltage when the ignition key is ON at terminals 40 for the engine (gray
                connector) and terminals 3 and 5 for the chassis and body builder connections respectively (black
                connector).
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">ECM Voltage Reference Diagnostics</emph>
            </para>
            <para>If multiple sensor codes are set, the V
                <subscript>REF</subscript>
                signal circuit can be open, or the signal groucircuit can be open. Follow troubleshooting procedures to
                determine if V
                <subscript>REF</subscript>
                circuits are at fault. The engine will not run without a valid V
                <subscript>REF</subscript>
                signal.
            </para>
